I'll solve this step by step. Let me first understand the problem and then create a solution.

The key insight is that we need a probability distribution P over 150,000 tokens where:
- KL(P||U) = 10.0
- KL(U||P) = 10.0

Let me think about this mathematically. For a uniform distribution U over n=150000 elements, U(i) = 1/n.

KL(P||U) = Σ P(i) * log(P(i) * n) = Σ P(i)*log(P(i)) + log(n) = -H(P) + log(n)
KL(U||P) = Σ (1/n) * log((1/n) / P(i)) = -log(n) - (1/n) * Σ log(P(i))

So KL(P||U) = log(n) - H(P) = 10.0
And KL(U||P) = -log(n) - mean(log(P)) = 10.0

This means H(P) = log(n) - 10.0 and mean(log(P)) = -log(n) - 10.0

Let me try a parametric approach - a distribution where one element has probability p and the remaining n-1 elements share the rest equally.



